>
> > You left out a very important factor, that is, that you have more heat
to
> > begin with (before detonation) created by more compression of the
mixture.
> > If all other things were equal and you got identical energy conversion
the
> > higher compression would leave more residual heat.
> >
> > >However, basic thermodynamics (Thermo I) shows
> > >that you are converting energy into mechanical
> > >motion. The more we convert, the less leftover
> > >heat we have.
